// PROBABILITY WEIGHT FORMULA:
// the formula is: p(x) =
// {
//   (m - c0) * (e ^ (-(x-c)^2 / (2v))) + c0,    x <= c
//   (m - c1) * (e ^ (-(x-c)^2 / (2v))) + c1,    x > c
// }
// 
// x = wave number starting from 0
// c = "center" field
// v = "variance" field (controls spread of probability distribution)
// m = "peak" field
// c0 = "constantL" field
// c1 = "constantR" field
//    note: if a field called "constant" is present, c0 and c1 are instead the value of the "constant" field.
// e = (constant) Euler's number
//
// a p(x) value of 1.0 (100%) means that it has a normal probability weight.
// a p(x) value of less than 0.01 (1%) means that the creature will not spawn.
// although probability weights are only meaningful relative to the probability weights of other creatures.
//
// playground: https://www.desmos.com/calculator/pcjo2sd6f2

